b (cut #3) represents a crucial dataset, which underlines the
presence of the doubly (not quarterly) degenerate Dirac points,
i.e., the long sought Weyl points. The ﬁrst striking observation is
that the Bi dispersions appear to be non-spin-degenerate in this
particular region of the BZ. This breaking of the spin-degeneracy
is key, and is not consistent with the AFM calculations.
